main event: Six observers watched a shiny silver colored object move slowly northward.
interesting points: The object was too high to be a helicopter, but did have a 'noise' that was like that of an aircraft.
A 13-year-old boy and his wife and two sons saw a UFO with a noise like a helicopter, but it was round and had a silver grayish color.
They watched the UFO for 15 to 20 minutes as it moved eastward and was visible until around 10:30 p.m.
The boy had a camera but it had disappeared by the time he got back to try to take pictures.
The description is consistent with that of an aircraft observation.
sighted object: Shiny silver colored object, round UFO with silver grayish color
witnesses: Six observers, 13-year-old boy, his wife and two sons
